claim.claim-text:
1. A planing device for removing weld beads on car sheet metal, comprising: 
a handle with a cylinder cover on front end thereof, and connected with a support frame pivotally; 
a support frame including: 
a pressure plate mounted on said cylinder cover, and a press knob mounted on said pressure plate; 
a guide plate extended out of a side surface, and both sides thereof furnished with parallel surfaces on both sides attached with a guide block of a guide frame; center of said guide plate furnished with a threaded hole; 
a clamp plate mounted on said guide plate; top of said clamp plate furnished with a cylindrical hole for receiving a thread sleeve, and a height-adjusting knob to be mounted in a threaded hole of said thread sleeve; 
a bearing block and a round hole furnished on front end thereof for receiving a washer and a bearing, and an end of a transmission shaft; 
a transmission assembly mounted on other side of said support frame so as to have a power transmitted to said transmission shaft via a pneumatic motor; 
a transmission shaft, of which one end mounted on a bearing in front end of said support frame and connected with said transmission assembly, while other end thereof being connected with a round milling cutter which being fastened in place with a screw; 
a guide frame having two symmetrical claws on both sides of a frame body thereof; bottom surface of said claws to be attached to sheet metal flatly; near end of said frame body having a guide block, of which side surface having a guide groove mounted on said guide plate; a limit groove of said guide block mounted with a guide sleeve, and then an adjusting knob mounted into a thread hole of said guide plate; said guide block furnished with a round hole facing said height-adjusting knob so as to receive said height-adjusting knob to extend into said limit groove, and being fastened in place with a retaining ring.
